snippet.textDisplay: Players like Wiggins man...people don’t get how much the team you are drafted to impacts your trajectory in the league man.  Fit matters.  Who coaches you matters.  Who plays with you matters.  The mentality.  Who runs your organization matters.  And y’all wanna put it all on indivual players....but not even just that!! You wanna judge Indiivual players with the same struggles differently! Some you make excuses for, some become the scapegoats lol.  Glad to see Wiggins go to a true professional franchise.  Yes sometimes a player is to blame, but at least now we get to see what’s what.  What minny Wiggins fualt? Or was minny the reason Wiggins didn’t become what we thought he could? ( tho lets be honest, he hasn’t been bad this year like cmon.  Also, in 2016/17 didn’t he drop like 23 ppg and have a good year and people started talking good about him ? Then jimmy butler came in etc...also had to try to find his spot with LaVine and towns trying to make a name for themselves as well etc.  idk.  I’m not trying to be too soft on players, I just don’t think y’all give a lot of them a fair shake and understand how tough the situation combined with the expectations can be for them)
